<li>
<div><div> <a href="/blog/interviews/africanish-womanhood-body-between-esinam-bediako-and-itoro-bassey-conversation" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Bediak-Anchor.jpg?itok=TlBeVFgM" width="250" height="175" alt="Photographs of Esinam Bediako and Itoro Bassey" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />
</a>
</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/interviews/africanish-womanhood-body-between-esinam-bediako-and-itoro-bassey-conversation">Africanish Womanhood, the Body in Between: Esinam Bediako and Itoro Bassey…</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/esinam-bediako" hreflang="en">Esinam Bediako</a>, <a href="/author/itoro-bassey" hreflang="en">Itoro Bassey</a>
</span></div>
